<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1370665" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=559%2C559&#038;ssl=1" alt="COVID-19: Nigeria recorded 25 new cases not 26 in April 3rd, NCDC apologises" width="559" height="559" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1 107w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=58%2C58&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=194%2C194&amp;ssl=1 194w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?resize=130%2C130&amp;ssl=1 130w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/NCDC-4.jpg?w=680&amp;ssl=1 680w" sizes="(max-width: 559px) 100vw, 559px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, on Saturday admitted an error in its Friday report that indicated Nigeria recorded 26 new coronavirus cases. NCDC noted the error was in the number of cases reported for Osun State. According to the Centre, “Of the 25 new cases reported, 1 case was inadvertently reported from Osun state. This case was from OYO STATE Elucidating, NCDC stated; “The 26th case was a repeat result of a previously confirmed case and NOT a new case” The previous report with the error posted by the Centre on Friday reads; “Twenty new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 11 in Lagos, 3 in the FCT, 3 in Edo, 2 in Osun & 1 in Ondo” The erroneously reported cases were 210, while the corrected and authentic case according to NCDC correction indicates 209 confirmed cases in Nigeria as at 3rd of April; 25 discharged and 4 fatalities. Clarifying the error in a statement released on Twitter, NCDC posted; “On 3rd of April 2020, we reported 26 new cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria. An error has been discovered in this report as follows: “There were 25 new cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria. The 26th case was a repeat result of a previously confirmed case and NOT a new case “Of the 25 new cases reported, 1 case was inadvertently reported from Osun state. This case was from OYO STATE The correct breakdown is as follows: Lagos- 11 Osun- 6 FCT- 3 Edo- 3 Ondo- 1 Oyo- 1 “As at 10:30 pm 3rd April, there are 209 confirmed cases 25 discharged 4 deaths For a breakdown of cases by states- http://covid19.ncdc.gov.ng Lagos- 109 FCT- 41 Osun- 20 Oyo- 9 Akwa Ibom- 5 Ogun- 4 Edo- 7 Kaduna- 4 Bauchi- 3 Enugu- 2 Ekiti- 2 Rivers-1 Benue- 1 Ondo- 1” The Centre, however, apologised for the error while assuring Nigerians of its commitment to transparency. “We regret the error in our announcement of new #COVID19 cases in Nigeria yesterday. The NCDC remains committed to ensuring transparency and accurate reporting of infectious disease cases in Nigeria” Vanguard News Nigeria. Victor Ogunyinka The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 20 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in Nigeria bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 210. In its update at 10.30 pm Friday night, NCDC also confirmed four deaths and 25 discharged cases. "Twenty new cases of #COVID19… April 3, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By Rasheed Sobowale The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed the death of a coronavirus (COVID-19) patient in Edo State. Vanguard gathered that the Centre, late Friday published the update of the coronavirus cases in Nigeria. The latest report indicated the confirmed cases to have risen to 210,… April 3, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By David Royal The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC has confirmed that the country's coronavirus cases have now risen to 210 on Friday, with four deaths recorded and 25 patients discharged. This was announced on the centre's verified twitter handle on Friday night. READ ALSO: Nigeria announces 20 new… April 4, 2020 In 